Commercial travel
Flight availability is restricted and subject to change, limited international flights and domestic flights are available while the state of emergency remains in force. Private charter flight options are also available. Information on commercial and private flight schedules is available on the Nassau Flight Services website. Airline contact information is available on the Lyden Pindling International Airport website.
There is currently no direct commercial air travel to and from The Bahamas to the UK. British Airways plan to resume flights on 31 May 2021. This is subject to change. You should refer to the BA website and call centre +1 877 767 7970 for more information. Departure via transit destinations such as the US, Jamaica, or Cuba may be possible for eligible travellers. This is subject to change at short notice. You should refer to the travel advice and restrictions before travelling.
The situation and rules vary across the islands. Guidelines on inter-island travel, including testing, travel health cards, and quarantine requirements are available from the Office of the Prime Minister and the Ministry of Tourism.
Details of the procedures to get a travel health card for domestic travel are available here.
Returning to the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK.
If you cannot leave Bahamas
If you cannot leave Bahamas at this time, see advice on staying in Bahamas during coronavirus
